itialization happens at build time, but I wonder if AWT might not be included or could fail later. Setting a system property to disable documentation commands could help, especially if `DocCommand` is an issue. I’m also thinking of modifying system properties temporarily during tests. Yet, I should ensure that any changes I make don’t impact the overall system negatively.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Modifying newHarness for Testing**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether I can change the default `newHarness` to set a property during the Groovysh construction. This would be a global setting that's restored afterward, allowing us to omit the `DocCommand` and avoid AWT-related issues. Currently, the `newHarness` method includes documentation, which might lead to problems with metadata if the native image is missing classes. To sidestep that, I think updating `newHarness` to disable the documentation temporarily makes sense. Alternatively, we could use a custom command registration for better testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Adjusting newHarness for Commands**\\n\\nI'm questioning if we should tweak `newHarness()` to use a custom registrar when it's null. The thing is, the dynamic evaluation needs an ImportCommand, but that’s missing in `registerCoreCommands`. I could consider adding that ImportCommand for our tests, but then the default commands might not function as expected. Maybe I should define `registerDefaultLikeCoreCommands` to include ImportCommand, although that would mean the command registry test wouldn't be using the default. Such a tricky balancing act!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IasbQHHzpyhKBQHn0T4vbDgt|fc_00c3b408ddede332016a017762401081a2a8adf1decef1c795", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.groovy/groovy-groovysh/4.0.24/src/test/groovy/org_apache_groovy/groovy_groovysh/Groovy_groovyshTest.groovy", "edits": [{"oldText": "        Binding binding = new Binding()\n        Groovysh shell = registrar == null\n                ? new Groovysh(binding, io)\n                : new Groovysh(Thread.currentThread().contextClassLoader, binding, io, registrar)\n        return new ShellHarness(shell, io, output, error)\n", "newText": "        Binding binding = new Binding()\n        Groovysh shell\n        if (registrar == null) {\n            String previousDocCommandSetting = System.getProperty('groovysh.disableDocCommand')\n            System.setProperty('groovysh.disableDocCommand', 'true')\n            try {\n                shell = new Groovysh(binding, io)\n            } finally {\n                if (previousDocCommandSetting == null) {\n                    System.clearProperty('groovysh.disableDocCommand')\n                } else {\n                    System.setProperty('groovysh.disableDocCommand', previousDocCommandSetting)\n                }\n            }\n        } else {\n            shell = new Groovysh(Thread.currentThread().contextClassLoader, binding, io, registrar)\n        }\n        return new ShellHarness(shell, io, output, error)\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1574, "output": 1010, "cacheRead": 55296, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57880, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778480981538, "responseId": "resp_00c3b408ddede332016a017756719481a2a628b820a48abb99"}}
